    "name": "Simon Britton",
    "profile": "Simon Britton was an ex. Singer-Songwriter & Recording Artist signed to various record labels including WEA Records, M&G Records, President Records, Clubscene Records, Steppin' Out Records and ZYX Records.  \r\n\r\nHe was one half of [a=Red Rhythm], the multi-award winning hit production, songwriting and remix team whose credits included Ashanti, Aaliyah, Atomic Kitten, Aggro Santos, Bananarama, Beverley Knight, Boyz II Men, Chaka Demus & Pliers, Cutfather & Joe, Eminem, Ginuwine, Jimmy Cliff, Kimberly Wyatt of The Pussycat Dolls, Kool & The Gang, Leona Lewis, Liberty X, Melanie C, Michael Jackson, Michelle Williams of Destiny's Child, Missy Elliot, Run-DMC, Sean Paul,  Sting, Timbaland, Toni Braxton and Usher.\r\n\r\nHe has gone on to produce and work with artists and writers including Alexandra Burke, Alexander O'Neal, Belouis Some, Beenie Man, Camo & Krooked, Chris Brown, Clean Bandit, David Gray, Gorgon City, Guy Chambers, Julian Lennon, Lisa Maffia, Mandrill, Morris Pleasure of Earth, Win",
